                        "content": "A client is admitted to a hospital with a diagnosis of diabetic ketoacidosis (DKA). The initial blood glucose level is 950 mg/dL (52.9 mmol/L). A continuous intravenous (IV) infusion of short-acting insulin is initiated, along with IV rehydration with normal saline. The serum glucose level is now decreased to 240 mg/dL (13.37 mmol/L). The nurse would prepare to administer which medication next?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nEmergency management of DKA focuses on correcting fluid and electrolyte imbalances and normalizing the serum glucose level. If the corrections occur too quickly, serious consequences, including hypoglycemia and cerebral edema, can occur. During management of DKA, when the blood glucose level falls to 250 to 300 mg/dL (13.9 to 16.7 mmol/L), the IV infusion rate is reduced and a dextrose solution is added to maintain a blood glucose level of about 250 mg/dL (13.9 mmol/L), or until the client recovers from ketosis. Fifty percent dextrose is used to treat hypoglycemia. NPH insulin is not used to treat DKA. Phenytoin is not a usual treatment measure for DKA.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Complex Care: Emergency Situations/Management\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Endocrine: Diabetes Mellitus\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Glucose Regulation\nStrategies: Strategic Words, Subject                          Test-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic word, next. Focus on the subject, management of DKA. Eliminate option 2 first, knowing that short-duration (rapid-acting) insulin is used in the management of DKA. Eliminate option 1 next, knowing that this is the treatment for hypoglycemia. Note the words the serum glucose level is now decreased to 240 mg/dL (13.7 mmol/L). This should indicate that the IV solution containing dextrose is the next step in the management of care.",
                        "id": "e23c43268f8649958f3d44b4ddff7eff",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "736860ddb4f24885886e25a50b9cb3f4",
                                "content": "Monitoring urine for ketones"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "e881e905dd85438b831a4015dbc5a7a1",
                                "content": "Intravenous potassium replacement"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "0ba8ce9bb5dd4da88137879a3a72d7d1",
                                "content": "Administration of intravenous insulin"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a817a02d26fd42e7a7b373e0b6bc19d5",
                                "content": "A bolus of 5% dextrose intravenously"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d2251b7651cd4b079d79e45141f8849d",
                                "content": "Administration of a liter of 0.9% NaCl intravenously"
                            }
                        ],
