                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is preparing to care for a client recovering from a subtotal thyroidectomy. Which supplies would the nurse have readily accessible for the care of this client? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAlthough not common, airway obstruction after thyroid surgery is an emergency situation. Therefore, oxygen, suction equipment, calcium gluconate (to treat tetany if it occurs), and a tracheostomy tube insertion set need to be readily available in the client's room. These items will be needed to treat this emergency situation. Therefore, options 2, 3, and 5 are correct. There is no reason that a tourniquet needs to be readily available; 50% glucose is used to treat severe hypoglycemia.\n\nClient Needs: Safe and Effective Care Environment\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Generate Solutions\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Complex Care: Emergency Situations/Management\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Endocrine: Thyroid Disorders\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Planning\nPriority Concepts: Safety, Caregiving\nStrategies: Subject                 Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, subtotal thyroidectomy. Think about the anatomical location of this surgery and the possible complications. This will assist in determining the equipment that needs to be readily available.",
                        "id": "fa718d278d614f698e9858ccfc3dd144",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
                ]
            },
